onramp.types_summary.title: What type of on-ramp would you like to create?
onramp.types_summary.description: Network hubs allow you to connect multiple virtual private clouds (VPCs) to Magic WAN over a shared VPN tunnel. Hubs are recommended to reduce cost and complexity when you have multiple VPCs to connect.
onramp.option.existing_hub.title: Connect an existing hub to Cloudflare
onramp.option.existing_hub.description: Select to reduce complexity if you have an existing network hub like an AWS Transit Gateway. Cloudflare will attach a new VPN tunnel to your existing hub. Note: Only AWS hubs are supported at this time.
onramp.option.new_hub.title: Create a new hub and connect it to Cloudflare
onramp.option.new_hub.description: Select if you have multiple VPCs to connect but do not have an existing hub. Cloudflare will create an AWS-based hub and attach a VPN tunnel. Note: Only AWS hubs are supported at this time.
onramp.option.vpc.title: Connect an existing VPC to Cloudflare
onramp.option.vpc.description: Select if you have one VPC to connect. Cloudflare will create a VPN tunnel directly to your VPC. Note: If you would like to add this VPC to a hub in the future, you will need to delete this on-ramp and create a new hub on-ramp.

mwan.terraform_download.modal.download_c: Download Terraform and continue with automated deployment?

Continuing will download a duplicate version of this on-ramp as a Terraform configuration. Cloudflare will create resources and deploy your on-ramp.<0></0><1>Note:</1> Deploying the Terraform version of this on-ramp at a later date will create resource conflicts.
mwan.terraform_download.modal.download_e: Are you sure you want to abandon deployment?

A Terraform configuration of your on-ramp will be downloaded. After download, you can deploy via Terraform or return to Cloudflare to deploy.<0></0><1>Note:</1> Deploying from both Terraform and Cloudflare will create resource conflicts.
mwan.terraform_download.modal.confirm_do: Are you sure you want to download Terraform for this on-ramp?

If this on-ramp was previously planned or deployed with Cloudflare, deploying with Terraform will attempt to create conflicting resources and fail. You can still download the file to read or use as a template without conflicts.
mwan.terraform_download.modal.confirm_pl: Are you sure you want to deploy this on-ramp with Cloudflare?
This on-ramp was previously downloaded as a Terraform configuration. If you deployed it outside of Cloudflare, continuing may cause cloud resource conflicts.
